# Tests

## Structure
- Mirror `src/`: tests under `tests/Context/{BoundedContext}/` with the same layers (Application, Domain, Infrastructure).
- Unit tests: `tests/Context/{BC}/Application/` and `tests/Context/{BC}/Domain/`.
- HTTP integration: `tests/Context/{BC}/Infrastructure/` (controllers).

## Naming
- Class: `{ClassUnderTest}Test` (e.g. `CreateAccountCommandHandlerTest`, `AccountTest`).
- Methods: descriptive of the scenario; `test_` prefix or `@test` annotations per project config.

## Object Mothers
- Use Mothers for valid test data: `tests/Context/{BC}/Domain/` or dedicated folder (e.g. `UserMother`, `SlipMother`).
- Mothers return entities, value objects, or arrays ready for tests; avoid duplicating fragile construction in each test.

## Unit tests (handlers / domain)
- Mock repositories and external dependencies (Mockery or PHPUnit mocks).
- Arrange–Act–Assert. Cover happy path and errors (domain exceptions, not found, etc.).
- Do not touch the database in pure unit tests.

## Integration tests (controllers)
- Extend the project's test base (e.g. `ApiTestCase`) and run real HTTP requests.
- Where possible, use transactions/rollback (e.g. dama/doctrine-test-bundle) instead of DROP/CREATE schema per test to keep speed.
- Assert HTTP response and, when relevant, side effects (events stored, state in DB).
